        public AgentBuilder.RedefinitionListenable with(AgentBuilder.RedefinitionStrategy.BatchAllocator redefinitionBatchAllocator)
        Description copied from interface: AgentBuilder.RedefinitionListenable.WithoutBatchStrategy
        A batch allocator is responsible for diving a redefining of existing types into several chunks. This allows to narrow down errors for the redefining of specific types or to apply a AgentBuilder.RedefinitionStrategy.Listener action between chunks.
        Specified by:
        with in interface AgentBuilder.RedefinitionListenable.WithoutBatchStrategy
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • with

        public AgentBuilder.RedefinitionListenable with(AgentBuilder.RedefinitionStrategy.Listener redefinitionListener)
        Description copied from interface: AgentBuilder.RedefinitionListenable

        A redefinition listener is invoked before each batch of type redefinitions and on every error as well as after the redefinition was completed. A redefinition listener can be used for debugging or logging purposes and to apply actions between each batch, e.g. to pause or wait in order to avoid rendering the current VM non-responsive if a lot of classes are redefined.

        Adding several listeners does not replace previous listeners but applies them in the registration order.

        Specified by:
        with in interface AgentBuilder.RedefinitionListenable
        Parameters:
        redefinitionListener - The listener to register.
        Returns:
        A new instance of this agent builder which notifies the specified listener upon type redefinitions.
